Description:
KAKEN- the database of Grants-in-Aid for Scientific Research- JAPAN contains the "Project Selected" documents and the research report summaries (incl. annual and final). The Grants-in-Aid for Scientific Research is granting whole field of science- and this database provides the latest information of the research projects in Japan.KAKEN is established and provided by the National Institute of Informatics (NII)- JAPAN with support of the Ministry of Education- Culture- Sports- Science and Technology (MEXT) and the Japan Society for the Promotion of Science (JSPS).It is a part of "GeNii- the National Institute of Informatics academic content portal"- established by NII.KAKEN defines two types of entity URIs- i.e.- research project URI and researcher URI. Each URI consists of project number and registered researcher number.For example- the project of which project number is 18049069 refers to:
http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/p/18049069
The researcher whose researcher number is 80143551 refers to:
http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/r/80143551
You can check these URIs by the following unix command.
$ curl --location --header "Accept: application/rdf+xml" "http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/p/18049069"
The KAKEN redirects to the generic document of project "18049069" which refers to:
http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/d/p/18049069
- and content negotiate for mimetype application/rdf+xml as you can get by the "curl" command.As for the researcher- you can check the following command. 
$ curl --location --header "Accept: application/rdf+xml" "http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/r/80143551"
The KAKEN redirects to the generic document of researcher "80143551" which refers to:
http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/d/r/80143551
- and content negotiate for mimetype application/rdf+xml as you can get by the "curl" command.OpenSearch API is useful to search projects and researchers of KAKEN. KAKEN provides application/atom+xml and application/rss+xml format to response. application/rss+xml is recommended to LOD users because the format is written in RDF compatibility sence.You can examine OpenSearch API for projects- such as:
$ curl "http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/x/opensearch/rss/p?q0=semantic&count=20&from=1"
You can also examine OpenSearch API for researchers- such as:
$ curl "http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/x/opensearch/rss/r?q0=semantic&count=20&from=1"
Sources: Web:http://kaken.nii.ac.jp Name:National Institute of Informatics Email:kaken_fdbk@nii.ac.jp
